description: Grand Designs House of the Year: Series 3 Technology Documentary hosted by Kevin McCloud, published by Channel 4 broadcasted as part of Ch4. series in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/f/f2/Grand-Designs-House-of-the-Year-Series-3-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Grand Designs House of the Year: Series 3 Kevin McCloud visits the country's most cutting edge homes as they compete for the 2017 Royal Institute of British Architects House of the Year 3) Homes in the Country Kevin McCloud, architect Damion Burrows and magazine editor Michelle Ogundehin review homes in the country. There's a luxurious tree house in Dorset that shows off the wonder of wood, and an awe-inspiring cantilevered concrete home on the Isle of Purbeck, with floor-to-ceiling glazing. Plus, a property with a cluster of zinc-clad boxes imitating local traditional Scottish farmsteads, and a 17th-century Devon barn that's been sensitively restored for modern living. But which will be shortlisted for the Royal Institute of British Architects House of the Year 2017?
